arbor$CD_Account <- as.factor(arbor$CD_Account)
arbor$Online <- as.factor(arbor$Online)
arbor$CreditCard <- as.factor(arbor$CreditCard)

#training our data
arbor_split <- initial_split(arbor, prop = 0.7)
arbor_train <- training(arbor_split)
arbor_test <- testing(arbor_split)
# We are making a random Forrest model
arbor_rf <- randomForest(Personal_Loan ~ ., data = arbor, ntree = 200, mtry = 8, importance = TRUE, keep.inbag = TRUE)
#Generate predictions using the random forest model in both training and testing datasets. Calculate the Accurary of the model
arbor_train_pred1 <- predict(arbor_rf, arbor_train)
arbor_test_pred1 <- predict(arbor_rf, arbor_test)
print(arbor_train_pred1)
